| DS-P1-001 | Critical | Partner auth/profile/account | Replace legacy `AllowAny` partner self-service with authenticated-principal-only access, remove raw `partner_session_token` lookups from profile, OTP, address, bank, withdrawal, logo, and password handlers, and stop serializing `partner_session_token`, `firebase_token`, and `web_firebase_token` in partner profile payloads. | open | Add partner API regressions that reject anonymous or foreign-token profile/bank/withdraw writes and confirm owner-only Bearer-authenticated reads and writes. Source: `partners/partner_profile.py:334-1295`; `partners/partner_accounts_and_transactions.py:15-344`; `partners/serializers.py:214-229` |
| DS-P1-002 | High | Partner booking fulfillment | Normalize partner booking mutations around the authenticated principal. Remove request-body/query `partner_session_token` rebinding from booking action, document, arrangement, complaint, close, and report endpoints so booking ownership comes from the auth helper only. | open | Add partner-booking regressions proving a foreign token cannot mutate another partner's booking, documents, complaints, or close/report routes. Source: `booking/manage_partner_booking.py:394-643`; `booking/manage_partner_booking.py:646-940`; `booking/manage_partner_booking.py:1378-1774` |
| DS-P1-003 | High | Booking documents and payouts | Enforce one-row-per-booking invariants for `DocumentsStatus` and `PartnersBookingPayment`, recalculate document completeness on delete/update, and stop creating duplicate receivable rows during repeated fulfillment transitions. | open | Add service/model tests for duplicate-row prevention, delete-triggered completion recompute, and idempotent payout creation across repeated document updates. Source: `booking/models.py:172-181`; `booking/models.py:266-279`; `booking/workflow.py:215-225`; `booking/manage_partner_booking.py:556-640`; `booking/services.py:734-766` |
| DS-P1-004 | High | Wallet withdrawals | Move balance validation inside a locked transaction for both customer and partner withdrawals and update wallet amounts with row locking or database-side arithmetic so concurrent requests cannot overdraw or lose updates. | open | Add concurrent withdrawal tests or transaction-level regressions proving two simultaneous requests cannot overdraw the same wallet. Source: `common/api_v1.py:218-256`; `partners/partner_accounts_and_transactions.py:235-264` |
| DS-P1-005 | Medium | Dead routes and duplicate package logic | Align maintained code with the live route surface: either mount or delete the unmounted management views, and clearly separate website-only legacy package code from the routed operator package write path so dead implementations stop drifting. | open | Add route inventory coverage or explicit deprecation tests showing which management/package views are intentionally live versus unreachable. Source: `management/urls.py:6-15`; `management/approval_task.py:907-990`; `management/approval_task.py:1282-1333`; `partners/urls.py:32-48`; `partners/package_management.py` |
| DS-P1-006 | Medium | Management QA coverage | Restore a dedicated `management` test module for company approval, payment review, receivable transfer, master hotels, and any intentionally unmounted admin views so follow-on fixes can be verified without rescanning the repo. | open | Reintroduce `management/tests.py` or `management/tests/*` and run `python3 manage.py test management partners booking common --settings=huz.settings_test` in a provisioned environment. Source: `rg --files /Users/macbook/Desktop/Huz/Huz-Backend/management`; `python3 manage.py test partners.tests booking.tests common.tests --settings=huz.settings_test` |
| OPT-P1-001 | High | Booking customer detail responses | Reuse a `select_related`/`prefetch_related` detail queryset for current-user booking retrieve and post-mutation responses so `DetailBookingSerializer` stops lazily loading company, address, payment, document, passport, arrangement, and rating relations per request. | verified | Implemented in `booking/services.py` and `booking/views/bookings.py`, with serializer/query regressions added in `booking/tests.py` for retrieve, payment, and passport detail responses. Re-verified by `.venv/bin/python manage.py test booking.tests.BookingWorkflowServiceValidationTests booking.tests.ManagePartnerBookingViewsTests booking.tests.BookingSerializerQueryTests --settings=huz.settings_test` (70 tests, OK) and `python3 -m compileall booking management huz`; the focused serializer regressions still observe 0 extra serialization queries on the preloaded detail path. |
| OPT-P1-002 | High | Partner dashboard and rating stats | Collapse partner dashboard counts and rating histograms into DB-side aggregates instead of per-bucket `.count()` loops and Python iteration over every rating row. | verified | Implemented in `booking/manage_partner_booking.py`, with bounded-query regressions added for `/bookings/get_overall_booking_statistics/`, `/bookings/get_overall_partner_rating/`, and `/bookings/get_overall_rating_package_wise/`. Re-verified by `.venv/bin/python manage.py test booking.tests.BookingWorkflowServiceValidationTests booking.tests.ManagePartnerBookingViewsTests booking.tests.BookingSerializerQueryTests --settings=huz.settings_test` (70 tests, OK); current budgets remain <=2 queries for booking stats and overall rating plus <=3 queries for package rating. |
| OPT-P1-003 | High | Admin payment review queue | Replace the queue-count fan-out on the annotated `reviewable_queryset` with filtered aggregates so `/management/fetch_all_paid_bookings/` does not rerun the same join-heavy review query for each counter and summary value. | verified | Implemented in `management/approval_task.py`, with a bounded-query regression added for `/management/fetch_all_paid_bookings/`. Re-verified by `.venv/bin/python manage.py test booking.tests.BookingWorkflowServiceValidationTests booking.tests.ManagePartnerBookingViewsTests booking.tests.BookingSerializerQueryTests --settings=huz.settings_test` (70 tests, OK) and `python3 -m compileall booking management huz`; the focused queue regression still holds the response to <=7 queries while preserving aggregate queue metadata. |
| OPT-P1-004 | Medium | Operator hotel catalog fallback | Stop loading and deduplicating the full `HuzHotelDetail` table in Python when the synthetic master-hotel package is missing; push dedupe/limit logic into the database or enforce canonical source data before serialization. | open | Add fallback-path coverage for `/partner/get_all_hotels_with_images/` that seeds non-catalog hotels and asserts bounded query count and bounded result size under city/search filters. Source: `partners/package_management_operator.py:1392-1429` |
| REG-P0-001 | High | Route compatibility and legacy endpoint removal | The live working tree removes multiple legacy customer, admin, website, and chat routes, including older `/common/*` self-service endpoints, customer-facing `/bookings/*` endpoints, several `/management/*` report routes, `/partner/get_city_wise_packages_count/`, and `/chat/`. If any downstream client still depends on those paths, the change is externally breaking and cannot be fully validated inside Huz-Backend alone. | open | In the regression sweep, smoke the live route table and confirm the missing endpoints are intentional. If consumer apps still call them, treat restoration or migration as downstream coordination work rather than a same-lane backend-only fix. Source: `common/urls.py`; `booking/urls.py`; `management/urls.py`; `partners/urls.py`; `huz/urls.py` |
| SEC-001 | Critical | `common/authentication.py`, `partners/partner_profile.py`, `partners/partner_accounts_and_transactions.py`, `booking/manage_partner_booking.py` | Legacy session-token transport is still accepted across customer and partner flows, including high-value mutation routes, so bearer-equivalent secrets can still travel in query strings and request bodies. | open | Source inspection during security-audit Phase 0 |
